      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Grignard reagents react with oxetane, a four-membered cyclic ether, to yield primary alcohols, but the reaction is much slower than the corresponding reaction with ethylene oxide. Suggest a reason for the difference in reactivity between oxetane and ethylene oxide.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcmNYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--601dba8cf8f2698decab5c25dda616d68deebcb8/OChem_18_EC_046.jpg\" alt=\"Oxetane (four-membered ring incorporating one oxygen) reacts with R Mg X, then hydronium, to produce R C H 2 C H 2 C H 2 O H.\">",
